Lastly, the presence of additional aromatic rings generally adds around +20°C per ring. The overall estimated melting point for dantrolene including the base benzophenone, one nitro group, hydantoin, azo group, and three total aromatic rings would thus be around 218°C (48 + 40 + 100 + 10 + 20).
